From  (G23) aganakteo; indignation -- indignation. see GREEK  (G23) aganakteo
Perhaps from agan (much); to love (in a social or moral sense) -- (be-)love(-ed). Compare  (G5368) phileo. see GREEK  (G5368) phileo
From  (G25) agapao; love, i.e. Affection or benevolence; specially (plural) a love-feast -- (feast of) charity(-ably), dear, love. see GREEK  (G25) agapao
From  (G25) agapao; beloved -- (dearly, well) beloved, dear. see GREEK  (G25) agapao
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1904) Hagar); Hagar, the concubine of Abraham -- Hagar. see HEBREW  (H1904) Hagar
Of foreign origin (compare  (H104) 'iggra'); properly, to be a courier, i.e. (by implication) to press into public service -- compel (to go). see HEBREW  (H104) 'iggra'
From aggos (a pail, perhaps as bent; compare the base of  (G43) agkale); a receptacle -- vessel. see GREEK  (G43) agkale
From  (G32) aggelos; an announcement, i.e. (by implication) precept -- message. see GREEK  (G32) aggelos

Imperative of  (G71) ago; properly, lead, i.e. Come on -- go to. see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G71) ago (compare  (G32) aggelos); a drove -- herd. see GREEK  (G71) ago see GREEK  (G32) aggelos
From  (G1) a (as negative particle) and  (G1075) genealogeo; unregistered as to birth -- without descent. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1075) genealogeo
From  (G1) a (as negative particle) and  (G1085) genos; properly, without kin, i.e. (of unknown descent, and by implication) ignoble -- base things. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1085) genos
From  (G40) hagios; to make holy, i.e. (ceremonially) purify or consecrate; (mentally) to venerate -- hallow, be holy, sanctify. see GREEK  (G40) hagios
From  (G37) hagiazo; properly, purification, i.e. (the state) purity; concretely (by Hebraism) a purifier -- holiness, sanctification. see GREEK  (G37) hagiazo
Neuter of  (G40) hagios; a sacred thing (i.e. Spot) -- holiest (of all), holy place, sanctuary. see GREEK  (G40) hagios

From hagos (an awful thing) (compare  (G53) hagnos,  (G2282) thalpo); sacred (physically, pure, morally blameless or religious, ceremonially, consecrated) -- (most) holy (one, thing), saint. see GREEK  (G53) hagnos see GREEK  (G2282) thalpo
From  (G40) hagios; sanctity (i.e. Properly, the state) -- holiness. see GREEK  (G40) hagios
From  (G40) hagios; sacredness (i.e. Properly, the quality) -- holiness. see GREEK  (G40) hagios
From agkos (a bend, "ache"); an arm (as curved) -- arm.
From the same as  (G43) agkale; a hook (as bent) -- hook. see GREEK  (G43) agkale
From the same as  (G43) agkale; an "anchor" (as crooked) -- anchor. see GREEK  (G43) agkale
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and the same as  (G1102) gnapheus; properly, unfulled, i.e. (by implication) new (cloth) -- new. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1102) gnapheus
From  (G53) hagnos; cleanliness (the quality), i.e. (specially) chastity -- purity. see GREEK  (G53) hagnos
From  (G53) hagnos; to make clean, i.e. (figuratively) sanctify (ceremonially or morally) -- purify (self). see GREEK  (G53) hagnos
From  (G48) hagnizo; a cleansing (the act), i.e. (ceremonially) lustration -- purification. see GREEK  (G48) hagnizo

column7: to be ignorant, not to know
column8: be ignorant, not know, not understand
column9: From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3539) noieo; not to know (through lack of information or intelligence); by implication, to ignore (through disinclination) -- (be) ignorant(-ly), not know, not understand, unknown. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3539) noieo
From  (G50) agnoeo; a thing ignored, i.e. Shortcoming -- error. see GREEK  (G50) agnoeo
From  (G50) agnoeo; ignorance (properly, the quality) -- ignorance. see GREEK  (G50) agnoeo

column7: free from ceremonial defilement, holy, sacred
column9: From the same as  (G40) hagios; properly, clean, i.e. (figuratively) innocent, modest, perfect -- chaste, clean, pure. see GREEK  (G40) hagios
From  (G53) hagnos; cleanness (the state), i.e. (figuratively) blamelessness -- pureness. see GREEK  (G53) hagnos
Adverb from  (G53) hagnos; purely, i.e. Honestly -- sincerely. see GREEK  (G53) hagnos
From  (G1) a (as negative particle) and  (G1108) gnosis; ignorance (properly, the state) -- ignorance, not the knowledge. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1108) gnosis
From  (G1) a (as negative particle) and  (G1110) gnostos; unknown -- unknown. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1110) gnostos

From ageiro (to gather; probably akin to  (G1453) egeiro); properly, the town-square (as a place of public resort); by implication, a market or thoroughfare -- market(-place), street. see GREEK  (G1453) egeiro

column7: to buy in the marketplace, purchase
column9: From  (G58) agora; properly, to go to market, i.e. (by implication) to purchase; specially, to redeem -- buy, redeem. see GREEK  (G58) agora

column7: pertaining to the marketplace, an agitator
column9: From  (G58) agora; relating to the market-place, i.e. Forensic (times); by implication, vulgar -- baser sort, low. see GREEK  (G58) agora
From  (G71) ago; (abstractly) a catching (of fish); also (concretely) a haul (of fish) -- draught. see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G1) a (as negative particle) and  (G1121) gramma; unlettered, i.e. Illiterate -- unlearned. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1121) gramma

column8: live outdoors, abide in the field.
column9: From  (G68) agros and  (G832) auleo (in the sense of  (G833) aule); to camp out -- abide in the field. see GREEK  (G68) agros see GREEK  (G832) auleo see GREEK  (G833) aule
From  (G61) agra; to hunt, i.e. (figuratively) to entrap -- catch. see GREEK  (G61) agra
From  (G66) agrios and  (G1636) elaia; an oleaster -- olive tree (which is) wild. see GREEK  (G66) agrios see GREEK  (G1636) elaia

column7: living in the fields, wild, savage, fierce
column9: From  (G68) agros; wild (as pertaining to the country), literally (natural) or figuratively (fierce) -- wild, raging. see GREEK  (G68) agros

column7: Agrippa, the name of two descendant of Herod the Great
column9: Apparently from  (G66) agrios and  (G2462) hippos; wild-horse tamer; Agrippas, one of the Herods -- Agrippa. see GREEK  (G66) agrios see GREEK  (G2462) hippos
From  (G71) ago; a field (as a drive for cattle); genitive case, the country; specially, a farm, i.e. Hamlet -- country, farm, piece of ground, land. see GREEK  (G71) ago
Ultimately from  (G1) a (as negative particle) and  (G5258) hupnos; to be sleepless, i.e. Keep awake -- watch. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5258) hupnos
From  (G69) agrupneo; sleeplessness, i.e. A keeping awake -- watch. see GREEK  (G69) agrupneo

column8: be, bring forth, carry, let go.
column9: A primary verb; properly, to lead; by implication, to bring, drive, (reflexively) go, (specially) pass (time), or (figuratively) induce -- be, bring (forth), carry, (let) go, keep, lead away, be open.
Reduplicated from  (G71) ago; a bringing up, i.e. Mode of living -- manner of life. see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G71) ago; properly, a place of assembly (as if led), i.e. (by implication) a contest (held there); figuratively, an effort or anxiety -- conflict, contention, fight, race. see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G73) agon; a struggle (properly, the state), i.e. (figuratively) anguish -- agony. see GREEK  (G73) agon

column7: to contend for a prize, struggle
column9: From  (G73) agon; to struggle, literally (to compete for a prize), figuratively (to contend with an adversary), or genitive case (to endeavor to accomplish something) -- fight, labor fervently, strive. see GREEK  (G73) agon
Of Hebrew origin ( (H121) 'Adam); Adam, the first man; typically (of Jesus) man (as his representative) -- Adam. see HEBREW  (H121) 'Adam
From  (G1) a (as negative particle); and  (G1160) dapane; costless, i.e. Gratuitous -- without expense. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1160) dapane
Probably of Hebrew origin (compare  (H5716) adiy); Addi, an Israelite -- Addi. see HEBREW  (H5716) adiy
Fem of  (G80) adephos; a sister (naturally or ecclesiastically) -- sister. see GREEK  (G80) adephos
From  (G1) a (as a connective particle) and delphus (the womb); a brother (literally or figuratively) near or remote (much like  (G1) a) -- brother. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1) a
From  (G80) adephos; brotherhood (properly, the feeling of brotherliness), i.e. The (Christian) fraternity -- brethren, brotherhood. see GREEK  (G80) adephos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G1212) delos; hidden, figuratively, indistinct -- appear not, uncertain. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1212) delos
From  (G82) adelos; uncertainty -- X uncertain. see GREEK  (G82) adelos
Adverb from  (G82) adelos; uncertainly -- uncertainly. see GREEK  (G82) adelos
From a derivative of adeo (to be sated to loathing); to be in distress (of mind) -- be full of heaviness, be very heavy.

column7: Hades, the abode of departed spirits
column9: From  (G1) a (as negative particle) and  (G1492) eido; properly, unseen, i.e. "Hades" or the place (state) of departed souls -- grave, hell. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1492) eido
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G1252) diakrino; properly, undistinguished, i.e. (actively) impartial -- without partiality. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1252) diakrino

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a compound of  (G1223) dia and  (G3007) leipo; unintermitted, i.e. Permanent -- without ceasing, continual. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3007) leipo
Adverb from  (G88) adialeiptos; uninterruptedly, i.e. Without omission (on an appropriate occasion) -- without ceasing. see GREEK  (G88) adialeiptos

From a derivative of a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G1311) diaphtheiro; incorruptibleness, i.e. (figuratively) purity (of doctrine) -- uncorruptness. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1311) diaphtheiro

column8: hurt, injure, be an offender, be unjust.
column9: From  (G94) adikos; to be unjust, i.e. (actively) do wrong (morally, socially or physically) -- hurt, injure, be an offender, be unjust, (do, suffer, take) wrong. see GREEK  (G94) adikos

column8: evil doing, iniquity, matter of wrong.
column9: From  (G91) adikeo; a wrong done -- evil doing, iniquity, matter of wrong. see GREEK  (G91) adikeo

From  (G94) adikos; (legal) injustice (properly, the quality, by implication, the act); morally, wrongfulness (of character, life or act) -- iniquity, unjust, unrighteousness, wrong. see GREEK  (G94) adikos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G1349) dike; unjust; by extension wicked; by implication, treacherous; specially, heathen -- unjust, unrighteous. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1349) dike
Adverb from  (G94) adikos; unjustly -- wrongfully. see GREEK  (G94) adikos

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G1384) dokimos; unapproved, i.e. Rejected; by implication, worthless (literally or morally) -- castaway, rejected, reprobate. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1384) dokimos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle}; and  (G1388) dolos; undeceitful, i.e. (figuratively) unadulterated -- sincere. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1388) dolos

column7: of Adramyttium, a seaport of Mysia
column9: From Adramutteion (a place in Asia Minor); Adramyttene or belonging to Adramyttium -- of Adramyttium.

column7: the Adriatic, the name of a sea
column9: From Adria (a place near its shore); the Adriatic sea (including the Ionian) -- Adria.
From hadros (stout); plumpness, i.e. (figuratively) liberality -- abundance.
From  (G102) adunatos; to be unable, i.e. (passively) impossible -- be impossible. see GREEK  (G102) adunatos

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G1415) dunatos; unable, i.e. Weak (literally or figuratively); passively, impossible -- could not do, impossible, impotent, not possible, weak. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1415) dunatos
To sing -- sing.
From an obsolete primary noun (apparently meaning continued duration); "ever,"by qualification regularly; by implication, earnestly; --always, ever.
From the same as  (G109) aer; an eagle (from its wind-like flight) -- eagle. see GREEK  (G109) aer

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2219) zume; unleavened, i.e. (figuratively) uncorrupted; (in the neutral plural) specially (by implication) the Passover week -- unleavened (bread). see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2219) zume
Of Hebrew origin (compare  (H5809) Azzuwr); Azor, an Israelite -- Azorigin see HEBREW  (H5809) Azzuwr

From aemi (to breathe unconsciously, i.e. Respire; by analogy, to blow); "air" (as naturally circumambient) -- air. Compare  (G5594) psucho. see GREEK  (G5594) psucho
From a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2288) thanatos; deathlessness -- immortality. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2288) thanatos

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of themis (statute; from the base of  (G5087) tithemi); illegal; by implication, flagitious -- abominable, unlawful thing. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2316) theos; godless -- without God. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2316) theos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G5087) tithemi (in the sense of enacting); lawless, i.e. (by implication) criminal -- wicked. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi

column7: to do away with what has been laid down, set aside
column8: cast off, despise, bring to nought, reject.

From  (G114) atheteo; cancellation (literally or figuratively) -- disannulling, put away. see GREEK  (G114) atheteo

column9: Plural of Athene (the goddess of wisdom, who was reputed to have founded the city); Athenoe, the capitol of Greece -- Athens.
From  (G116) Athenai; an Athenoean or inhabitant of Athenae -- Athenian. see GREEK  (G116) Athenai
From athlos (a contest in the public lists); to contend in the competitive games -- strive.
From  (G118) athleo; a struggle (figuratively) -- fight. see GREEK  (G118) athleo
From a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2372) thumos; to be spiritless, i.e. Disheartened -- be dismayed. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2372) thumos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and probably a derivative of  (G5087) tithemi (meaning a penalty); not guilty -- innocent. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From aix (a goat); belonging to a goat -- goat.
From aisso (to rush) and  (G251) hals (in the sense of the sea; a beach (on which the waves dash) -- shore. see GREEK  (G251) hals
From  (G125) Aiguptos; an ?Gyptian or inhabitant of ?Gyptus -- Egyptian. see GREEK  (G125) Aiguptos

column7: Egypt, the land of the Nile
column8: The land of the Nile, Egypt.
column9: Of uncertain derivation -- ?Gyptus, the land of the Nile -- Egypt.
From  (G104) aei; everduring (forward and backward, or forward only) -- eternal, everlasting. see GREEK  (G104) aei

Perhaps from  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G1492) eido (through the idea of downcast eyes); bashfulness, i.e. (towards men), modesty or (towards God) awe -- reverence, shamefacedness. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1492) eido
From aitho (to scorch) and ops (the face, from  (G3700) optanomai); an ?Thiopian (as a blackamoor) -- Ethiopian. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
Of uncertain derivation; blood, literally (of men or animals), figuratively (the juice of grapes) or specially (the atoning blood of Christ); by implication, bloodshed, also kindred -- blood.
From  (G129) haima and a derivative of  (G1632) ekcheo; an effusion of blood -- shedding of blood. see GREEK  (G129) haima see GREEK  (G1632) ekcheo

column8: diseased with an issue of blood.
column9: From  (G129) haima and  (G4482) rheo; to flow blood, i.e. Have a hoemorrhage -- diseased with an issue of blood. see GREEK  (G129) haima see GREEK  (G4482) rheo

column7: Aeneas, a paralytic cured by Peter
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Aeneas, an Israelite -- Aeneas.
From  (G134) aineo; a praising (the act), i.e. (specially) a thank(-offering) -- praise. see GREEK  (G134) aineo
From  (G136) ainos; to praise (God) -- praise. see GREEK  (G136) ainos
From a derivative of  (G136) ainos (in its primary sense); an obscure saying ("enigma"), i.e. (abstractly) obscureness -- X darkly. see GREEK  (G136) ainos
Apparently a prime word; properly, a story, but used in the sense of  (G1868) epainos; praise (of God) -- praise. see GREEK  (G1868) epainos

column7: Aenon, a place in the Jordan Valley
column9: Of Hebrew origin (a derivative of  (H5869) ayin, place of springs); ?Non, a place in Palestine -- ?Non. see HEBREW  (H5869) ayin
Probably akin to  (G142) airo; to take for oneself, i.e. To prefer -- choose. Some of the forms are borrowed from a cognate hellomai hel'-lom-ahee; which is otherwise obsolete. see GREEK  (G142) airo
From  (G138) haireomai; properly, a choice, i.e. (specially) a party or (abstractly) disunion -- heresy (which is the Greek word itself), sect. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
From a derivative of  (G138) haireomai; to make a choice -- choose. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
From the same as  (G140) hairetizo; a schismatic -- heretic (the Greek word itself). see GREEK  (G140) hairetizo

A primary root; to lift up; by implication, to take up or away; figuratively, to raise (the voice), keep in suspense (the mind), specially, to sail away (i.e. Weigh anchor); by Hebraism (compare  (H5375) nasa') to expiate sin -- away with, bear (up), carry, lift up, loose, make to doubt, put away, remove, take (away, up). see HEBREW  (H5375) nasa'
Of uncertain derivation; to apprehend (properly, by the senses) -- perceive.
From  (G143) aisthanomai; perception, i.e. (figuratively) discernment -- judgment. see GREEK  (G143) aisthanomai
From a derivative of  (G143) aisthanomai; properly, an organ of perception, i.e. (figuratively) judgment -- senses. see GREEK  (G143) aisthanomai
From  (G150) aischros and kerdos (gain); sordid -- given to (greedy of) filthy lucre. see GREEK  (G150) aischros

column8: for the sake of dishonest gain.

From  (G150) aischros and  (G3056) logos; vile conversation -- filthy communication. see GREEK  (G150) aischros see GREEK  (G3056) logos
Neuter of  (G150) aischros; a shameful thing, i.e. Indecorum -- shame. see GREEK  (G150) aischros
From the same as  (G153) aischunomai; shameful, i.e. Base (specially, venal) -- filthy. see GREEK  (G153) aischunomai
From  (G150) aischros; shamefulness, i.e. Obscenity -- filthiness. see GREEK  (G150) aischros
From  (G153) aischunomai; shame or disgrace (abstractly or concretely) -- dishonesty, shame. see GREEK  (G153) aischunomai
From aischos (disfigurement, i.e. Disgrace); to feel shame (for oneself) -- be ashamed.

column8: ask, beg, call for, crave, desire.

From  (G154) aiteo; a thing asked or (abstractly) an asking -- petition, request, required. see GREEK  (G154) aiteo

From the same as  (G154) aiteo; a cause (as if asked for), i.e. (logical) reason (motive, matter), (legal) crime (alleged or proved) -- accusation, case, cause, crime, fault, (wh-)ere(-fore). see GREEK  (G154) aiteo
From a derivative of  (G156) aitia; a thing charged -- complaint. see GREEK  (G156) aitia
Neuter of  (G159) aitios; a reason or crime (like  (G156) aitia) -- cause, fault. see GREEK  (G159) aitios see GREEK  (G156) aitia
From the same as  (G154) aiteo; causative, i.e. (concretely) a causer -- author. see GREEK  (G154) aiteo

From a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G5316) phaino (compare  (G1810) exaiphnes) (meaning non-apparent); unexpected, i.e. (adverbially) suddenly -- sudden, unawares. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5316) phaino see GREEK  (G1810) exaiphnes
From  (G164) aichmalotos; captivity -- captivity. see GREEK  (G164) aichmalotos
From  (G164) aichmalotos; to capture (like  (G163) aichmalotizo) -- lead captive. see GREEK  (G164) aichmalotos see GREEK  (G163) aichmalotizo

column8: lead away captive, bring into captivity.

From aichme (a spear) and a derivative of the same as  (G259) halosis; properly, a prisoner of war, i.e. (genitive case) a captive -- captive. see GREEK  (G259) halosis

column7: a space of time, an age

Compare  (G5550) chronos. see GREEK  (G104) aei see GREEK  (G5550) chronos
From  (G165) aion; perpetual (also used of past time, or past and future as well) -- eternal, for ever, everlasting, world (began). see GREEK  (G165) aion
From  (G169) akathartos; impurity (the quality), physically or morally -- uncleanness. see GREEK  (G169) akathartos
From  (G169) akathartos; impurity (the state), morally -- filthiness. see GREEK  (G169) akathartos

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G2508) kathairo (meaning cleansed); impure (ceremonially, morally (lewd) or specially, (demonic)) -- foul, unclean. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2508) kathairo

From a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2540) kairos (meaning unseasonable); to be inopportune (for oneself), i.e. To fail of a proper occasion -- lack opportunity. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2540) kairos
Adverb from the same as  (G170) akaireomai; inopportunely -- out of season. see GREEK  (G170) akaireomai
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2556) kakos; not bad, i.e. (objectively) innocent or (subjectively) unsuspecting -- harmless, simple. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2556) kakos
Probably from the same as  (G188) akmen; a thorn -- thorn. see GREEK  (G188) akmen
From  (G173) akantha; thorny -- of thorns. see GREEK  (G173) akantha
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2590) karpos; barren (literally or figuratively) -- without fruit, unfruitful. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2590) karpos

column7: not to be condemned, beyond reproach
column9: From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2607) kataginosko; unblamable -- that cannot be condemned. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2607) kataginosko
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a compound of  (G2596) kata and  (G2572) kalupto; unveiled -- uncovered. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2572) kalupto
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2632) katakrino; without (legal) trial -- uncondemned. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2632) katakrino
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2647) kataluo; indissoluble, i.e. (figuratively) permanent -- endless. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2647) kataluo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2664) katapauo; unrefraining -- that cannot cease. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2664) katapauo
From  (G182) akatastatos; instability, i.e. Disorder -- commotion, confusion, tumult. see GREEK  (G182) akatastatos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2525) kathistemi; inconstant -- unstable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2525) kathistemi
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2722) katecho; unrestrainable -- unruly. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2722) katecho

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G2767) kerannumi; unmixed, i.e. (figuratively) innocent -- harmless, simple. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2767) kerannumi
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2827) klino; not leaning, i.e. (figuratively) firm -- without wavering. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2827) klino
From the same as  (G188) akmen; to make a point, i.e. (figuratively) mature -- be fully ripe. see GREEK  (G188) akmen

From  (G1) a (as a particle of union) and keleuthos (a road); properly, to be in the same way with, i.e. To accompany (specially, as a disciple) -- follow, reach. see GREEK  (G1) a

From  (G193) akrates; want of self-restraint -- excess, incontinency. see GREEK  (G193) akrates
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2904) kratos; powerless, i.e. Without self-control -- incontinent. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2904) kratos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G2767) kerannumi; undiluted -- without mixture. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2767) kerannumi
From the same as  (G196) akribestatos; exactness -- perfect manner. see GREEK  (G196) akribestatos

Adverb from the same as  (G196) akribestatos; exactly -- circumspectly, diligently, perfect(-ly). see GREEK  (G196) akribestatos
Apparently from the same as  (G206) akron; a locust (as pointed, or as lighting on the top of vegetation) -- locust. see GREEK  (G206) akron
From  (G202) akroates; an audience-room -- place of hearing. see GREEK  (G202) akroates
From akroaomai (to listen; apparently an intensive of  (G191) akouo); a hearer (merely) -- hearer. see GREEK  (G191) akouo

column7: at the extreme angle or corner
column9: From  (G206) akron and  (G1137) gonia; belonging to the extreme corner -- chief corner. see GREEK  (G206) akron see GREEK  (G1137) gonia

column7: the top of a heap, the best of the spoils
column9: From  (G206) akron and this (a heap); properly (in the plural) the top of the heap, i.e. (by implication) best of the booty -- spoils. see GREEK  (G206) akron
Neuter of an adjective probably akin to the base of  (G188) akmen; the extremity -- one end... Other, tip, top, uttermost participle see GREEK  (G188) akmen
Probably for Latin aquila (an eagle); Akulas, an Israelite -- Aquila.
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2964) kuroo; to invalidate -- disannul, make of none effect. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2964) kuroo

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G1635) hekon; unwilling -- against the will. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1635) hekon
Neuter of alabastros (of uncertain derivation), the name of a stone; properly, an "alabaster" box, i.e. (by extension) a perfume vase (of any material) -- (alabaster) box.
From  (G213) alazon; braggadocio, i.e. (by implication) self-confidence -- boasting, pride. see GREEK  (G213) alazon
From ale (vagrancy); braggart -- boaster.
From alale (a shout, "halloo"); to vociferate, i.e. (by implication) to wail; figuratively, to clang -- tinkle, wail.
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2980) laleo; unspeakable -- unutterable, which cannot be uttered. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2980) laleo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2980) laleo; mute -- dumb. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2980) laleo
From  (G251) hals; salt; figuratively, prudence -- salt. see GREEK  (G251) hals
From  (G1) a (as particle of union) and the base of  (G3045) liparos; to oil (with perfume) -- anoint. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3045) liparos
From  (G220) alektor and  (G5456) phone; cock-crow, i.e. The third night-watch -- cockcrowing. see GREEK  (G220) alektor see GREEK  (G5456) phone
From aleko (to ward off); a cock or male fowl -- cock.
From Alexandreia (the city so called); an Alexandreian or inhabitant of Alexandria -- of Alexandria, Alexandrian.
From the same as  (G221) Alexandreus; Alexandrine, or belonging to Alexandria -- of Alexandria. see GREEK  (G221) Alexandreus

column7: Alexander, a son of Simon of Cyrene, also a coppersmith, also two Jews
column9: From the same as (the first part of)  (G220) alektor and  (G435) aner; man-defender; Alexander, the name of three Israelites and one other man -- Alexander. see GREEK  (G220) alektor see GREEK  (G435) aner
From aleo (to grind); flour -- meal.
From  (G227) alethes; truth -- true, X truly, truth, verity. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From  (G227) alethes; to be true (in doctrine and profession) -- speak (tell) the truth. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2990) lanthano; true (as not concealing) -- true, truly, truth. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2990) lanthano
From  (G227) alethes; truthful -- true. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From the same as  (G224) aleuron; to grind -- grind. see GREEK  (G224) aleuron
Adverb from  (G227) alethes; truly -- indeed, surely, of a surety, truly, of a (in) truth, verily, very. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From  (G251) hals; a sailor (as engaged on the salt water), i.e. (by implication) a fisher -- fisher(-man). see GREEK  (G251) hals
From  (G231) halieus; to be a fisher, i.e. (by implication) to fish -- go a-fishing. see GREEK  (G231) halieus
From  (G251) hals; to salt -- salt. see GREEK  (G251) hals
From alisgeo (to soil); (ceremonially) defilement -- pollution.

column7: otherwise, on the other hand, but
column9: Neuter plural of  (G243) allos; properly, other things, i.e. (adverbially) contrariwise (in many relations) -- and, but (even), howbeit, indeed, nay, nevertheless, no, notwithstanding, save, therefore, yea, yet. see GREEK  (G243) allos
From  (G243) allos; to make different -- change. see GREEK  (G243) allos

column8: some other way, from somewhere else
column9: From  (G243) allos; from elsewhere -- some other way. see GREEK  (G243) allos
From  (G243) allos and agoreo (to harangue (compare  (G58) agora)); to allegorize -- be an allegory (the Greek word itself). see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G58) agora
Of Hebrew origin (imperative of  (H1984) halal and  (H3050) Yahh); praise ye Jah!, an adoring exclamation -- alleluiah. see HEBREW  (H1984) halal see HEBREW  (H3050) Yahh

Genitive plural from  (G243) allos reduplicated; one another -- each other, mutual, one another, (the other), (them-, your-)selves, (selves) together (sometimes with  (G3326) meta or  (G4314) pros). see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G3326) meta see GREEK  (G4314) pros
From  (G243) allos and  (G1085) genos; foreign, i.e. Not a Jew -- stranger. see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G1085) genos
Middle voice of apparently a primary verb; to jump; figuratively, to gush -- leap, spring up.
A primary word; "else," i.e. Different (in many applications) -- more, one (another), (an-, some an-)other(-s, -wise).

column7: one who meddles in things alien to his calling
column9: From  (G245) allotrios and  (G1985) episkopos; overseeing others' affairs, i.e. A meddler (specially, in Gentile customs) -- busybody in other men's matters. see GREEK  (G245) allotrios see GREEK  (G1985) episkopos
From  (G243) allos; another's, i.e. Not one's own; by extension foreign, not akin, hostile -- alien, (an-)other (man's, men's), strange(-r). see GREEK  (G243) allos
From  (G243) allos and  (G5443) phule; foreign, i.e. (specially) Gentile -- one of another nation. see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G5443) phule
Adverb from  (G243) allos; differently -- otherwise. see GREEK  (G243) allos
From the same as  (G257) halon; to tread out grain -- thresh, tread out the corn. see GREEK  (G257) halon
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3056) logos; irrational -- brute, unreasonable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3056) logos
Of foreign origin (compare  (G174) akanthinos); aloes (the gum) -- aloes. see GREEK  (G174) akanthinos
A primary word; "salt" -- salt.
From  (G251) hals; briny -- salt. see GREEK  (G251) hals
Comparative of a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3077) lupe; more without grief -- less sorrowful. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3077) lupe
Of uncertain derivation; a fetter or manacle -- bonds, chain.
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and the base of  (G3081) lusitelei; gainless, i.e. (by implication) pernicious -- unprofitable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3081) lusitelei
Of Hebrew origin (compare  (H2501) Cheleph); Alphoeus, an Israelite -- Alpheus. see HEBREW  (H2501) Cheleph
Probably from the base of  (G1507) heilisso; a threshing-floor (as rolled hard), i.e. (figuratively) the grain (and chaff, as just threshed) -- floor. see GREEK  (G1507) heilisso
Of uncertain derivation; a fox, i.e. (figuratively) a cunning person -- fox.

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G3133) maraino; unfading, i.e. (by implication) perpetual -- that fadeth not away. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3133) maraino

column7: to miss the mark, do wrong, sin

From  (G264) hamartano; a sin (properly abstract) -- offence, sin(-ful). see GREEK  (G264) hamartano
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a form of  (G3144) martus; unattested -- without witness. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3144) martus

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3334) metakineo; immovable -- unmovable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3334) metakineo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G3338) metamellomai; irrevocable -- without repentance, not to be repented of. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3338) metamellomai

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3392) miaino; unsoiled, i.e. (figuratively) pure -- undefiled. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3392) miaino

Apparently a primary word; a lamb -- lamb.

From  (G288) ampelos; a vineyard -- vineyard. see GREEK  (G288) ampelos
Contracted for Latin ampliatus (enlarged); Amplias, a Roman Christian -- Amplias.

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3469) momaomai; unblamable -- blameless. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3469) momaomai

Of Hebrew origin ( (H526) 'Amown); Amon, an Israelite -- Amon. see HEBREW  (H526) 'Amown

column7: Amos, an Israelite ancestor of Christ
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H531) 'Amowts); Amos, an Israelite -- Amos. see HEBREW  (H531) 'Amowts

column7: usually untranslatable, but generally denoting supposition, wish, possibility or uncertainty
column9: A primary particle, denoting a supposition, wish, possibility or uncertainty -- (what-, where-, wither-, who-)soever. Usually unexpressed except by the subjunctive or potential mood. Also contracted for  (G1437) ean. see GREEK  (G1437) ean

column7: as a preposition denotes upwards, up, as a prefix denotes up, again, back
column9: A primary preposition and adverb; properly, up; but (by extension) used (distributively) severally, or (locally) at (etc.) -- and, apiece, by, each, every (man), in, through. In compounds (as a prefix) it often means (by implication) repetition, intensity, reversal, etc.

column9: From  (G303) ana and  (G1097) ginosko; to know again, i.e. (by extension) to read -- read. see GREEK  (G303) ana see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko

column7: be made known, make oneself known
column8: be made known, make oneself known.
